Dear colleagues:
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text>
I sincerely appreciate each of you for all you've done this Fall semester. As always, you have continued to further HSUâ€™s goal of providing a positive, meaningful educational experience for our students. Also, thank you to everyone who has engaged in the planning of our many University initiatives and in our emergency operations efforts.
    </mj-text>
        <mj-text>
In gratitude, I am authorizing staff to end their work three hours prior to the end of their workday on Wednesday, Nov. 24. To ensure that necessary work is completed, appropriate administrators must approve this paid informal time off.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>
        There is no need for employees to record this time off in PeopleSoft, unless they have scheduled vacation on Wednesday. Employees who have scheduled vacation time off on Wednesday should record eight hours of vacation taken in PeopleSoft, and then unofficially take off three hours at a later date. Employees who work their full shift Wednesday will be allowed three hours of informal (not recorded in PeopleSoft) time to be taken prior to June 30, 2022, with the approval of their appropriate administrator.

        </mj-text>
					</mj-column>
